@startuml PY-003 Sequence Diagram — Error to Friendly Message

title PY-003: Runtime Error → API Call → Friendly Message Displayed

actor Learner
participant "TryItTabPanel\n(browser)" as Panel
participant "Pyodide\n(browser WASM)" as Pyodide
participant "POST /api/explain-error\n(Next.js route handler)" as API
participant "Claude Haiku\n(Anthropic API)" as Haiku
participant "OutputPanel" as Output

== Code runs and fails ==

Learner -> Panel : clicks Run
Panel -> Pyodide : runPythonAsync(code)
Pyodide --> Panel : throws — raw traceback

== Friendly error flow ==

Panel -> Output : show loading state\n("Explaining error…")
Panel -> API : POST { code, rawError }
note right of API
  Runs server-side.
  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY never
  reaches the browser.
end note

API -> Haiku : messages: [\n  system: encourage, plain English,\n           one paragraph, no jargon\n  user: "Code: {code}\nError: {rawError}"\n]

alt Haiku responds within timeout
  Haiku --> API : friendly explanation string
  API --> Panel : { explanation }
  Panel -> Output : display FriendlyMessage\nin var(--accent-orange)
  Panel -> Output : render TechnicalToggle\n(hidden by default)
else API timeout or error
  API --> Panel : { fallback: true }
  Panel -> Output : display static fallback message\n"Something went wrong — check your\ncode for typos and try again!"
end

== Learner inspects raw error ==

Learner -> Output : clicks "Show technical detail"
Output -> Output : expand RawTraceback\naria-expanded=true
Output --> Learner : sees raw Python traceback

Learner -> Output : clicks "Hide technical detail"
Output -> Output : collapse RawTraceback\naria-expanded=false

@enduml
